      <h1 class='title'>Evidence to be produced where respondent not present etc.</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='grand-committee-report-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 cc299-300GC</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_299gc' title='Col. 299GC &mdash; HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c299GC' name='column_299gc' href='#column_299gc' rel='bookmark'>299GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-03875'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_486' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        11 (1) This paragraph applies if the respondent&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) is not present, or</li>
        <li>(b) is not represented by counsel or a solicitor,</li></ol>
        at the hearing of an application for an order under this Part.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-03876'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_487' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (2) The court must not make an order under this Part unless there is produced to it such evidence as may be prescribed by rules of court of&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) the consent of the respondent to the making of the order,</li>
        <li>(b) the financial resources of the respondent, and</li>
        <col>GC 300</col>
        <li>(c) if the financial provision specified in the application includes or consists of provision in respect of a child of the family to be made by the applicant to the respondent for the benefit of the child or to the child, the financial resources of the child.</li></ol>
      </p>
